📖 What is Wireshark?

Wireshark is a free and open-source network protocol analyzer.

It captures network packets traveling through your computer or network and allows you to inspect them in detail.

Think of Wireshark as a microscope for network traffic.

Instead of guessing what is happening on the network, Wireshark lets you see the actual packets.

Why Do We Need Wireshark?

Suppose you open a website and it loads very slowly.

Possible reasons include:

DNS problem
Network congestion
Packet loss
TCP retransmissions

