Installing Wireshark on Ubuntu
sudo apt update
sudo apt install wireshark

During installation, you may be asked whether non-root users should be allowed to capture packets.

Choose Yes if appropriate for your environment.

Launch Wireshark
wireshark
Capture Packets
Select your network interface (such as Wi-Fi or Ethernet).
Click Start Capturing.
Generate some traffic (for example, open a website or run ping).
Stop the capture.
Analyze the packets.
Linux Commands

List network interfaces:

ip link

View network connections:

ss -tuln

Generate ICMP traffic:

ping google.com

Capture packets from the command line using tcpdump:

sudo tcpdump -i any

Save captured packets to a file:

sudo tcpdump -i any -w capture.pcap
